### Shard Sizing Math

```
SHARD SIZING CALCULATION
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Rule of thumb: 10-50GB per shard for good performance

Estimated index size (searchable fields only):
  - 10TB raw data
  - Index ~10% of fields for search
  - Compression ratio ~40%
  - = 10TB × 0.10 × 0.40 = ~400GB index

Shard strategy:
  - 12 primary shards × ~35GB = 420GB total
  - 1 replica = 840GB total index storage

Node sizing:
  - 3 nodes × 300GB storage = 900GB ✓
  - Each node: 8 vCPU, 32GB RAM
  - Heap: 16GB per node (50% of RAM)
  - OS cache: remaining 16GB (critical for performance)

Time-based sharding option (if data is time-series):
  - Monthly indices: content_2024_01, content_2024_02...
  - Alias "content_current" → latest index
  - Old indices: reduce replicas to 0, force merge
  - Saves ~60% storage on cold data
```

